Rating: 4
Delicious & attractive company dish that goes well with any main course. I halved recipe except for the onion, and used chicken broth instead of water. After bringing rice mixture to a simmer on stovetop, I transferred it to the rice cooker and let it finish there. I fried almonds to a darker, caramel color and added them to the onions and currants (that I had soaked in water) at the last minute.

Rating: 2
It was very mild, so if you are serving it with a dish with a strong sauce that would be good, but it doesn't stand on its own. Adding cumin helps. Not worth the cost of the saffron, I would just use turmeric next time. It was very pretty looking.

Rating: 4
I made this for a dinner party and was told by my guests that they could not leave without the recipe. I cut the recipe by 1/2, made the rice the night before, reheated and then spooned in the almonds, currants and onions just prior to serving. My currants seemed on the dry side so I plumped them in boiling water for about 15 min. (I did this the night before too, drained and then refrigerated). Even cutting the recipe by 1/2, it generously served 4 with leftovers. Highly recommended...will become a standard in our house.

