Beautiful dish. I used just a little less saffron but other than that, followed the recipe. The rice is brilliantly yellow and frosted with the currant mixture is a lovely presentation on a buffet. I made the day before and reheated in the oven covered at about 275. It was a hit.

Rating: 4
Made this last night for Passover. Absolutely fabulous! The flavors are out of this world. I will make this again with other entrees. The rice turned out perfectly (I made it the day before and reheated in the microwave just before serving.) I added the onion/almond/currant mixture after reheating the rice and zapped it all for one more minute in the microwave. A keeper.